        "content": "<p>The following simple fact does not currently seem to be in Mathlib.  Is it worth adding it (possibly even as a simp lemma)?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Finset</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">range</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Finset</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Iio</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">ext</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">m</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">only</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Finset</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mem_range</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Finset</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mem_Iio</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 464738166,
        "sender_full_name": "Terence Tao",
        "timestamp": 1724444323
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Nat.Iio_eq_range#doc\">docs#Nat.Iio_eq_range</a></p>",
        "id": 464738530,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1724444402
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>OK, I have no idea how I missed that. Thanks.</p>\n<p>EDIT: I reconstructed how I got here.  I started with<code>example (n:ℕ) : Finset.range n = Finset.Iio n</code>, which for some reason does not close by <code>exact?</code>, <code>hint</code>, or <code>apply?</code>, though <code>aesop</code> can handle it.  Then I decided to delete the variable <code>n</code> without rechecking whether it now closed.</p>",
        "id": 464738701,
        "sender_full_name": "Terence Tao",
        "timestamp": 1724444430
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think that we should drop <code>Finset.range</code> and use <code>Finset.Iio</code>, but I'm too lazy to do the refactor.</p>",
        "id": 464738893,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1724444479
